@node PKLUDGE "Work-around for DLG %x{}{} problem"

MenuThing generates the %x{}{} sequences at the end of the menu for
every hidden menu command, that is, every menu command for which you
did not create a smart menu item.  The %x{}{} sequence allows the user
to use hotkeys to interrupt the menu display.

There are some menu keys that DLG incorrectly parses in a %x{}{}
sequences.  At this time I am aware of the following: space, ~, and |.
MenuThing knows about these, and will not generate the sequence for
them.  There may be more, in which case you might see the %x{}{}
displayed at the end of your menu.

You can use a binary editor such as "newzap" to add more keys to the
list.  Simply search the MenuThing executable for the string
"0123456789|~" and add any new keys that don't work to the end of this
string.  There are approximately 10 bytes of null characters available
here.  This is an interim solution until the DLG bug fix is distributed.

If you are uncomfortable using newzap, you can instead manually remove
the broken %x{}{} sequence from the end of your menu files, but you will
have to do this every time you generate your menus.
@endnode

@node HISTORY "Change History"

@{b}Version 1.0 (18-Sep-1993)@{ub}

 · First public release of MenuThing.

 · Added @{"Reset ANSI sequence" link RESET} option to the menu set window.

 · Changed "Amiga ANSI" terminology to "Amiga ISO".  The supplied
   Basic_ISO.style is simply the old Basic_ANSI.style renamed.  Beta
   testers will need to edit their menu sets to use the correct style,
   or rename the style file to the old name.

 · Due to a bug in DLG v1.0 and earlier, MenuThing does not generate
   the hotkeyed %x{}{} commands for space, ~, and | commands.  If you
   see stray %x{}{} sequences displayed at the end of your menu, a
   @{"work-around" link PKLUDGE} exists while you wait for the DLG
   bug fix to appear.

@{b}Version 0.3ß (7-Sep-1993)@{ub}

 · Menu sets with very long names no longer clobber the input path.

 · [<] is now correctly parsed as < instead of ].  Similar sequences of
   one style of bracket surrounded by another style are parsed correctly.

 · Fixed enforcer hits that could occur after opening the file requester
   multiple times.

 · Added more documentation on how to @{"plan" link PLAN} your menu sets.
   Hopefully this will clarify some of the more confusing aspects of the
   program.
     
 · Menu set 0 data is now displayed when entering the Menu Set window.

 · Set the environment variable MENUTHING if you want to install your
   MenuThing files somewhere other than the default.  If MENUTHING is
   not set, the directory DOORS:MenuThing will be used.

 · MenuThing now cross-checks your *.mth source with DLG's *.menun files.
   Discrepencies between the two are noted in error messages.

 · Custom menu output now includes %codes for commands defined in the
   DLG *.menun files that are not in *.mth.  This causes hot keys to
   work for all commands, not just the ones shown in the *.mth file.

@{b}Version 0.2ß (31-Aug-1993)@{ub}

 · Added the "gamma" blip to recognize the right-most character in a
   menu item as the menu character.  See @{"Blips" SYSTEM "doors:MenuThing/blips"} for details.

 · @{"Generate Menus" link GEN} now stops at the first error in each menu file,
   reducing the cascade of error requesters when you make a mistake.

 · Added a new option to Menu Sets:  @{"Allow Background Colors" link BACK}.

@{b}Version 0.1ß (28-Aug-1993)@{ub}

 · First beta release.  The only known bug is in the title screen. :-)

@endnode
